item.title: [+533] Mars Rover Spirit May Never Wake from Deep Sleep
item.description: One of NASA’s six-year-old Mars rovers missed its winter wake-up call, prompting concerns that it may never recover from the frigid cold. During previous winters, Spirit was able to get to a sun-facing slope in Gusev Crater before the deep cold set in, a position that left it able to draw enough power from its solar cells to keep heaters turned on
